cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper is about natural language processing and deep learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses multi-task learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new scheme for information sharing, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The experiments conducted in the paper involve text classification, which could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories, as text classification is a common task in both areas.
